WEBVTT

00:01.969 --> 00:09.743
**

00:09.777 --> 00:17.251
**

00:17.285 --> 00:25.126
**

00:25.159 --> 00:32.700
**

00:32.733 --> 00:35.136
I was late!
It's okay, sweetie.
It's not your fault.

00:35.169 --> 00:36.770
I just wanted to play
one more game at Gary's.

00:36.804 --> 00:39.107
Well, you did great.
You called 911 right away.

00:39.140 --> 00:40.641
He looked dead.
Daddy's not dead.

00:40.674 --> 00:42.310
He's gonna be okay,
right?

00:42.343 --> 00:43.811
He had a stroke.
That's not possible!

00:43.844 --> 00:45.813
Well, the CT confirmed
a ruptured aneurysm.

00:45.846 --> 00:47.415
We have to operate
to clip the bleeding

00:47.448 --> 00:48.782
and reduce
intracranial pressure.

00:48.816 --> 00:50.318
No, he had a stroke
six years ago.

00:50.351 --> 00:52.553
They put him on
diltiazem.

00:52.586 --> 00:53.854
We're gonna take good care
of your dad.

00:53.887 --> 00:57.258
**

00:57.291 --> 01:00.461
Naja Modi -- 28 years old,
suffered a burn to her left hand

01:00.494 --> 01:02.463
as a result
of a cooking accident.

01:02.496 --> 01:05.633
Are Jared and I
being punished?

01:07.468 --> 01:10.604
This is not a very
interesting case, is it?

01:10.638 --> 01:12.240
Lesson one --

01:12.273 --> 01:14.208
Don't suggest
to the the head of surgery

01:14.242 --> 01:15.743
that working with
the head of surgery

01:15.776 --> 01:17.345
is form of punishment.

01:17.378 --> 01:21.282
Dr. Melendez is
very unhappy with Jared

01:21.315 --> 01:23.317
for how
he got his job back.

01:23.351 --> 01:26.387
And Dr. Melendez is unhappy
with me for t-taking --

01:26.420 --> 01:27.888
taking two days off.

01:27.921 --> 01:31.592
I don't think he wants to talk
about this, Shaun.

01:31.625 --> 01:34.228
[ Monitor beeping rhythmically ]

01:34.262 --> 01:35.263
[ Groans ]

01:35.296 --> 01:36.697
I was an idiot.

01:36.730 --> 01:39.300
It's on the stove.
Of course it's hot, right?

01:39.333 --> 01:41.602
You wouldn't believe how often
we see these types of accidents.

01:41.635 --> 01:43.404
Well, there are
a lot of idiots.

01:43.437 --> 01:45.639
Okay, what do we need
to do here, Murphy?

01:45.673 --> 01:48.142
A superficial
partial-thickness burn

01:48.176 --> 01:49.677
should be managed
conservatively.

01:49.710 --> 01:51.745
Cleanse the area,
debride with soft gauze,

01:51.779 --> 01:54.148
and then cover
with an antimicrobial

01:54.182 --> 01:55.316
petroleum dressing.

01:55.349 --> 01:56.484
All of which means,

01:56.517 --> 01:58.752
this should heal
with minimal scarring.

01:58.786 --> 02:00.288
[ Gasps ]

02:00.321 --> 02:02.456
Naja, are you having
chest pain?

02:02.490 --> 02:03.924
I think I'm having
a heart attack.

02:03.957 --> 02:05.226
It's hard to breathe.

02:05.259 --> 02:07.761
Just relax if you can.

02:07.795 --> 02:09.530
Put her on oxygen,
a 12 lead EKG,

02:09.563 --> 02:10.931
and order a portable
chest X-ray.

02:10.964 --> 02:12.166
Murphy, let's move.
Come on.

02:12.200 --> 02:14.468
Her vitals are stable.

02:14.502 --> 02:16.704
**

02:16.737 --> 02:18.206
What the hell is
going on here?

02:18.239 --> 02:20.208
I don't know.

02:20.241 --> 02:22.543
But it is interesting.

02:22.576 --> 02:25.513
-- Captions by VITAC --

02:25.546 --> 02:32.553
**

02:35.489 --> 02:37.358
We've got a subarachnoid
hemorrhage. Suction.

02:37.391 --> 02:39.593
I need to isolate
the aneurysm.

02:39.627 --> 02:41.829
Poor kid.

02:41.862 --> 02:44.465
Imagine finding your dad
like that.

02:44.498 --> 02:46.600
Well, that's exactly
how I want to die.

02:46.634 --> 02:48.402
[ Sighs ]

02:48.436 --> 02:49.337
If the dad doesn't
make it,

02:49.370 --> 02:51.372
the kid will always remember
that moment --

02:51.405 --> 02:52.640
be traumatized by it.

02:52.673 --> 02:54.342
Because he loves him.

02:54.375 --> 02:56.677
The idea of dying without
anybody getting hurt --

02:56.710 --> 02:59.313
There's nothing sadder than
an empty waiting room.

03:02.015 --> 03:04.518
Okay, what do you see?

03:04.552 --> 03:06.954
A bulge on the anterior
communicating artery.

03:06.987 --> 03:08.756
Yeah, the ruptured aneurysm
is compromising

03:08.789 --> 03:10.424
blood flow
to the frontal lobe.

03:10.458 --> 03:12.393
Prep an 11 millimeter
standard clip.

03:12.426 --> 03:13.861
Are you married?

03:13.894 --> 03:15.463
Not anymore.

03:15.496 --> 03:18.299
Turns out he had even worse
judgment than I did.

03:18.332 --> 03:20.601
Oh, speaking of creeps,
you hear Coyle got transferred?

03:20.634 --> 03:22.770
[ Chuckles ] I'm so glad
they shut him down.

03:22.803 --> 03:25.005
Well, yeah, I guess.

03:25.038 --> 03:27.608
Just wish they'd spent the money
on a Pediatric Trauma Pod.

03:27.641 --> 03:29.877
**

03:29.910 --> 03:33.447
They gave him a raise.

03:33.481 --> 03:35.849
Clip.

03:35.883 --> 03:37.651
The EKG confirmed

03:37.685 --> 03:39.320
you weren't
having a heart attack.

03:39.353 --> 03:40.988
I-I wasn't faking.

03:41.021 --> 03:41.789
I wouldn't do that.

03:41.822 --> 03:43.457
We know.

03:43.491 --> 03:44.425
The imaging
also confirmed

03:44.458 --> 03:46.327
that you have considerable
lung inflammation.

03:46.360 --> 03:47.828
Is it possible
you inhaled smoke?

03:47.861 --> 03:49.363
I guess I must have.

03:49.397 --> 03:51.699
There was a minor
grease fire.

03:51.732 --> 03:52.566
What happens now?

03:52.600 --> 03:54.735
You need a bronchoscopy.

03:54.768 --> 03:56.670
We put a camera down your throat
to see how much damage there is

03:56.704 --> 03:58.572
and what we need to do
to repair it.

03:58.606 --> 04:00.308
But don't worry.
You'll be sedated.

04:00.341 --> 04:01.509
Please don't.

04:01.542 --> 04:02.943
Oh, I'm -- I'm sorry.

04:02.976 --> 04:04.512
The test is absolutely
necessary.

04:04.545 --> 04:05.779
The test is fine.

04:05.813 --> 04:06.814
But, um...

04:06.847 --> 04:09.583
please don't touch me,
except for medical purposes.

04:09.617 --> 04:11.051
Yeah, of course.

04:11.084 --> 04:16.357
**

04:16.390 --> 04:20.561
That does not
make sense.

04:20.594 --> 04:22.330
A number of religions have rules
about touching.

04:22.363 --> 04:23.531
I don't quite get it,
but --

04:23.564 --> 04:24.698
That makes sense.

04:24.732 --> 04:26.367
People shouldn't
touch people

04:26.400 --> 04:27.735
unless there's
a very good reason.

04:27.768 --> 04:29.970
Okay, then...

04:30.003 --> 04:31.772
what doesn't
make sense?

04:31.805 --> 04:34.442
The grease fire.

04:34.475 --> 04:36.043
The grease fire explains
the whole thing --

04:36.076 --> 04:37.711
the burn, the smoke.

04:37.745 --> 04:41.349
She told us she forgot
the stove was hot.

04:41.382 --> 04:42.850
How can you forget
something's hot

04:42.883 --> 04:44.084
when it is on fire?

04:44.117 --> 04:45.586
[ Snickers ] Shaun,

04:45.619 --> 04:46.787
I'm sure we would have heard
more of the story

04:46.820 --> 04:50.524
if she hadn't suddenly thought
she was having a heart attack.

04:50.558 --> 04:54.928
**

04:54.962 --> 04:56.964
Why didn't you fire him?

04:56.997 --> 04:58.532
Because his story was different
than yours.

04:58.566 --> 05:01.369
And you believe
his story?

05:01.402 --> 05:02.936
I believe your story.

05:02.970 --> 05:04.972
But you can't prove it.

05:05.005 --> 05:06.740
And we simply can't
make a policy

05:06.774 --> 05:08.909
of believing every woman
who files a complaint

05:08.942 --> 05:10.010
against every man.

05:10.043 --> 05:12.112
[ Sighs ]

05:12.145 --> 05:15.082
After a few thousand years
of doing the opposite,

05:15.115 --> 05:16.717
it wouldn't kill us
to overcorrect.

05:16.750 --> 05:18.419
And the fact that
your boyfriend assaulted him

05:18.452 --> 05:20.454
took away
any leverage I had.

05:20.488 --> 05:21.789
I did what I could.

05:21.822 --> 05:23.891
I got him to take
a position

05:23.924 --> 05:26.727
where he has very little contact
with staff, with patients --

05:26.760 --> 05:27.795
outreach chair.

05:27.828 --> 05:29.597
And it's
a lousy assignment.

05:29.630 --> 05:31.499
Sooner or later,
he's gonna quit.

05:31.532 --> 05:33.801
And get a job
somewhere else.

05:33.834 --> 05:37.505
If you have any
better ideas...

05:37.538 --> 05:39.973
I look forward
to hearing them.

05:40.007 --> 05:45.713
**

05:45.746 --> 05:51.585
**

05:51.619 --> 05:54.655
Lim: You're very lucky.

05:54.688 --> 05:57.425
The aneurysm was in
a small communicating artery.

05:57.458 --> 05:58.859
We were able
to restore blood flow

05:58.892 --> 06:00.060
to the impacted
brain areas.

06:00.093 --> 06:01.462
He's gonna be okay.

06:01.495 --> 06:02.630
Thank God.

06:04.932 --> 06:07.535
**

06:07.568 --> 06:10.438
Is this what life is gonna be
like from now on?

06:10.471 --> 06:13.441
A-Are these things just going
to keep happening?

06:13.474 --> 06:15.443
We're gonna keep him here
for a few days,

06:15.476 --> 06:16.710
do some follow-up
testing,

06:16.744 --> 06:19.413
make some adjustments
to his medications.

06:19.447 --> 06:21.849
Hopefully, we'll find out
why this happened.

06:21.882 --> 06:24.518
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

06:24.552 --> 06:25.886
I have to go.

06:25.919 --> 06:27.721
**

06:27.755 --> 06:29.757
Another one?

06:29.790 --> 06:32.460
Post-operative imaging showed
a 26-millimeter aneurysm

06:32.493 --> 06:33.694
in the basilar artery.

06:33.727 --> 06:34.962
That size and location,

06:34.995 --> 06:36.564
we're looking at
a high risk of rupture.

06:36.597 --> 06:38.098
He must have a genetic
predisposition --

06:38.131 --> 06:40.200
maybe a connective
tissue disease?

06:40.233 --> 06:43.737
All academic till
we repair it.

06:43.771 --> 06:44.872
Melendez:
Through the pharynx

06:44.905 --> 06:47.441
and over
to Grandmother's house we go.

06:47.475 --> 06:51.645
There's the epiglottis
and the vocal cords.

06:51.679 --> 06:53.814
I know you're not happy that
I sued the hospital.

06:53.847 --> 06:55.148
But I'm not gonna apologize
for that.

06:55.182 --> 06:57.451
That makes it simple.

06:57.485 --> 06:59.453
I did it because
I want to be here.

06:59.487 --> 07:00.854
I believe I can learn
a lot from you,

07:00.888 --> 07:03.223
even from your doghouse.

07:03.256 --> 07:04.692
I just hope you give me
a chance, sir.

07:04.725 --> 07:05.726
[ Monitor beeps rhythmically ]

07:05.759 --> 07:08.028
There's the carina.

07:08.061 --> 07:10.498
Gonna pass into the mainstem
bronchus of the left lung.

07:10.531 --> 07:13.934
Is breaking up with your fiancée
traumatic?

07:13.967 --> 07:17.137
**

07:17.170 --> 07:19.172
When I saw a woman
get shot,

07:19.206 --> 07:21.041
everyone told me
it was traumatic

07:21.074 --> 07:22.943
and that I should
be going home.

07:22.976 --> 07:26.580
Should you
be going home?

07:26.614 --> 07:28.215
Give me a mucosal brush
for a cellular sample.

07:28.248 --> 07:29.149
Loading it now.

07:29.182 --> 07:31.619
How long does it take
to get over a breakup

07:31.652 --> 07:32.986
with the woman you love?

07:34.988 --> 07:36.624
I'm seeing
a lot of inflammation,

07:36.657 --> 07:37.825
but no smoke damage.

07:37.858 --> 07:39.827
That makes se-sense.

07:39.860 --> 07:41.762
I thought we were doing this
because she inhaled smoke.

07:41.795 --> 07:43.731
She said
she inhaled smoke.

07:43.764 --> 07:45.733
I didn't believe her.

07:45.766 --> 07:46.867
Whatever the cause,
the inflammation

07:46.900 --> 07:48.001
and the damage are real.

07:48.035 --> 07:50.137
Let's get
a mucosal biopsy.

07:50.170 --> 07:53.040
I move down here,
we --

07:53.073 --> 07:54.575
The scope breached
her bronchial wall.

07:54.608 --> 07:55.809
She's hemorrhaging.

07:55.843 --> 07:57.911
This is bad.
Prep the O.R.!

07:57.945 --> 07:59.780
Type and cross two units
of blood. We've gotta move!

08:04.685 --> 08:05.986
We know there was a burn.

08:06.019 --> 08:07.187
Was it something related
to the grease fire,

08:07.220 --> 08:08.922
or separate
coincidental injury?

08:08.956 --> 08:13.060
[ Monitor beeping rhythmically ]

08:13.093 --> 08:15.095
You don't have a theory,

08:15.128 --> 08:17.230
or are you refusing
to talk to Jared?

08:17.264 --> 08:18.866
Melendez: I didn't answer
because it doesn't matter

08:18.899 --> 08:20.233
until we can repair
this puncture

08:20.267 --> 08:22.903
before bacteria passes through
and spreads an infection.

08:22.936 --> 08:24.004
That's true.

08:24.037 --> 08:25.205
Cut this suture.

08:25.238 --> 08:27.641
Let's approximate the edges
with forceps.

08:27.675 --> 08:31.078
Are you and Jared
even now?

08:31.111 --> 08:33.647
He made a mistake.
So did you.

08:33.681 --> 08:35.182
Exactly what mistake
did I make?

08:35.215 --> 08:37.317
This breach was
your fault.

08:37.350 --> 08:39.052
**

08:39.086 --> 08:42.122
Is that traumatic?

08:42.155 --> 08:44.291
**

08:48.195 --> 08:50.564
I had breakfast
by myself.

08:50.598 --> 08:52.132
Where were you?

08:52.165 --> 08:54.635
I'm sorry. Were we supposed to
have breakfast this morning?

08:54.668 --> 08:55.936
I had an early consult.
[ Laughing ]

08:55.969 --> 08:59.339
Yes, we always have breakfast
on Mondays.

08:59.372 --> 09:00.574
We do?

09:00.608 --> 09:02.075
Every Monday.

09:02.109 --> 09:03.310
Every Monday.

09:03.343 --> 09:05.145
Thank you.

09:05.178 --> 09:09.082
Well, I guess our streak has
been broken then, huh?

09:09.116 --> 09:11.852
If someone punctures
the bronchus

09:11.885 --> 09:15.155
during a routine bronchoscopy,
that's a mistake, right?

09:15.188 --> 09:17.925
Well, I can't imagine
how it wouldn't be.

09:17.958 --> 09:19.660
Why?
What did you do, Shaun?

09:19.693 --> 09:23.130
I'm wondering if I need
to report Dr. Melendez.

09:23.163 --> 09:24.965
Dr. Melendez did that?

09:24.998 --> 09:27.034
The protocol is
very clear.

09:27.067 --> 09:30.137
I need to report it.

09:30.170 --> 09:33.641
But I've seen how Jared
is being treated.

09:33.674 --> 09:37.010
Will Dr. Melendez treat me badly
if I report this?

09:38.946 --> 09:40.013
He shouldn't,
obviously.

09:40.047 --> 09:43.283
But human nature
being what...

09:43.316 --> 09:45.252
Human nature?

09:47.688 --> 09:48.588
Shaun, you know what?

09:48.622 --> 09:51.391
You should make this decision
for yourself.

09:51.424 --> 09:55.195
**

09:55.228 --> 09:57.364
In fact -- In fact...

09:57.397 --> 09:59.066
you should to make
all your decisions yourself

09:59.099 --> 10:01.234
from here on in.

10:01.268 --> 10:04.137
That's what we agreed on,
right?

10:04.171 --> 10:09.977
**

10:10.010 --> 10:11.244
Have you considered

10:11.278 --> 10:12.312
an endovascular embolization
procedure?

10:12.345 --> 10:13.781
I have.

10:13.814 --> 10:14.882
It's a little less risky,

10:14.915 --> 10:16.083
but I haven't done as many,

10:16.116 --> 10:18.018
so I'm not sure which way
we're better off.

10:18.051 --> 10:19.687
You want me to check
the roster --

10:19.720 --> 10:21.922
see if there's somebody
available with more experience?

10:21.955 --> 10:25.425
I would like to assist,
but yes.

10:25.458 --> 10:27.060
Okay, here we go.

10:29.096 --> 10:30.297
No, he's not available.

10:30.330 --> 10:31.899
So make him available.

10:31.932 --> 10:33.333
I got a husband and father

10:33.366 --> 10:35.736
who presented with two aneurysms
in the last 12 hours.

10:35.769 --> 10:37.705
I'd rather not.

10:37.738 --> 10:40.941
This particular surgeon
was recently...

10:40.974 --> 10:43.010
transferred.

10:45.412 --> 10:47.047
[ Mug thuds on table ]

10:47.080 --> 10:49.149
Not a chance.

10:49.182 --> 10:52.753
Coyle is the best available
surgeon for the job.

10:52.786 --> 10:54.855
Coyle should've been fired,
and if he'd been fired,

10:54.888 --> 10:55.989
he wouldn't be available.
[ Sighs ]

10:56.023 --> 10:57.090
And if he wasn't
available,

10:57.124 --> 10:59.793
you would be the best person
for the job.

10:59.827 --> 11:01.895
Our ultimate duty is
to the patient.

11:01.929 --> 11:04.297
**

11:04.331 --> 11:07.067
No, it's not.

11:07.100 --> 11:09.036
You agree he should
have been fired.

11:09.069 --> 11:11.238
Of course.
Even if he was the
best doctor in this hospital,

11:11.271 --> 11:12.773
he should have been fired,
right?

11:12.806 --> 11:14.341
[ Sighs ] Yes.

11:14.374 --> 11:16.309
So some things have
to matter more

11:16.343 --> 11:18.846
than who is
the most skilled.

11:18.879 --> 11:21.281
If we forgive Coyle just because
he's good at something,

11:21.314 --> 11:24.251
what does he do next?

11:24.284 --> 11:26.253
Either he matters
or we matter.

11:35.863 --> 11:39.332
Were you upset
during the procedure?

11:39.366 --> 11:42.135
Did Murphy tell you
that I was "traumatized"?

11:42.169 --> 11:43.871
You think that I might have
almost killed a person

11:43.904 --> 11:45.038
because you dumped me?

11:45.072 --> 11:47.274
The fact that you're describing
it as "me dumping you"

11:47.307 --> 11:50.043
suggests
that you are upset.

11:50.077 --> 11:52.846
Look, I'm fine.
You're fine.

11:52.880 --> 11:53.981
Nobody's upset.

11:54.014 --> 11:55.916
Great.

11:55.949 --> 11:57.384
But you do understand

11:57.417 --> 11:59.386
that I have to ask you
these questions,

11:59.419 --> 12:00.988
that I need a statement
from you.

12:01.021 --> 12:02.990
Yes.

12:03.023 --> 12:04.825
Here's my statement --

12:04.858 --> 12:06.126
"I wasn't distracted.

12:06.159 --> 12:07.494
I didn't screw up."

12:07.527 --> 12:08.929
You get all that?

12:08.962 --> 12:10.530
[ Elevator bell dings ]

12:10.563 --> 12:19.472
**

12:19.506 --> 12:21.041
Your bronchus was punctured
during the procedure,

12:21.074 --> 12:22.309
but it's been repaired.

12:22.342 --> 12:25.012
How?
How could that happen?

12:25.045 --> 12:26.179
Why did you lie?

12:26.213 --> 12:28.248
You said that
you inhaled smoke,

12:28.281 --> 12:30.383
but there was no evidence
of smoke.

12:30.417 --> 12:32.820
So, what do you gain
by lying to your doctors?

12:32.853 --> 12:33.821
I wasn't lying.

12:33.854 --> 12:35.422
I was just...

12:35.455 --> 12:37.224
confused, I guess.

12:37.257 --> 12:38.558
I was in a lot of pain,

12:38.591 --> 12:40.794
and it was all happening
so fast.

12:40.828 --> 12:42.129
[ Grunts ]

12:42.162 --> 12:43.363
My stomach!

12:43.396 --> 12:45.532
Naja, what are you
feeling?

12:45.565 --> 12:47.901
It's really sore and...
I feel like I'm going to--

12:47.935 --> 12:49.136
[ Gasping ]

12:49.169 --> 12:51.138
Can we get some help
over here?!

12:51.171 --> 12:53.874
Four milligrams
of ondansetron.

12:53.907 --> 12:56.810
[ Retching ]
Airway inflammation,
abdominal pain, nausea.

12:56.844 --> 12:59.112
We need a full blood panel
and abdominal ultrasound.

12:59.146 --> 13:01.982
[ Coughing, retching ]

13:02.015 --> 13:05.518
The procedure will seal off
the aneurysm,

13:05.552 --> 13:09.389
but there will almost certainly
be some brain damage --

13:09.422 --> 13:12.826
anything from mild visual
or speech disturbances

13:12.860 --> 13:16.496
to significant paralysis.

13:16.529 --> 13:19.833
But without the surgery,
he'll die.

13:19.867 --> 13:29.109
**

13:29.142 --> 13:33.113
No. I-I won't consent
to the operation.

13:33.146 --> 13:36.316
There really isn't
a lot of choice here.

13:36.349 --> 13:37.517
Without the operation --

13:37.550 --> 13:40.854
After his first stroke,
it --

13:40.888 --> 13:44.524
it took him so long
to recover.

13:44.557 --> 13:49.362
It was frustrating
and painful for him.

13:49.396 --> 13:51.198
But he did recover.

13:51.231 --> 13:55.602
**

13:55.635 --> 14:00.007
He made it clear he'd never want
to live compromised.

14:00.040 --> 14:02.910
**

14:02.943 --> 14:04.411
[ Voice shaking ]
Excuse me.

14:04.444 --> 14:07.547
**

14:14.955 --> 14:18.025
Thank you for having breakfast
with me.

14:18.058 --> 14:19.893
My pleasure.

14:19.927 --> 14:22.229
People lie a lot,
don't they?

14:22.262 --> 14:23.563
No, I-I meant it, Shaun.

14:23.596 --> 14:24.597
I'm happy to spend time
with you.

14:24.631 --> 14:28.068
There are seven reasons
that I've thought of.

14:28.101 --> 14:31.271
There may even be more.

14:31.304 --> 14:34.307
Do people ever lie
without a reason?

14:34.341 --> 14:35.575
No.

14:41.448 --> 14:44.051
Reason number six.
I think you just lied.

14:44.084 --> 14:45.552
I think you just lied
to avoid something.

14:45.585 --> 14:47.420
You don't like
this conversation.

14:47.454 --> 14:49.923
Shaun, n--
Shaun, I'm sorry.

14:49.957 --> 14:52.492
I'm just --
just a little distracted.

14:52.525 --> 14:53.927
My aneurysm patient --

14:53.961 --> 14:56.196
We're treating him
with blood-pressure meds

14:56.229 --> 14:57.664
to try and avoid
a rupture.

14:57.697 --> 15:00.934
You should do
an endovascular embolization.

15:00.968 --> 15:02.269
He doesn't want one.

15:02.302 --> 15:03.536
It could leave him
with brain damage.

15:03.570 --> 15:05.538
I thought he was
unconscious.

15:05.572 --> 15:07.407
He is.

15:07.440 --> 15:09.576
His wife knows
what he wants.

15:09.609 --> 15:10.443
[ Chuckles ]

15:10.477 --> 15:12.712
It's amazing.
I just --

15:12.745 --> 15:15.215
I don't think
I'd be able to do that.

15:15.248 --> 15:18.018
She's sacrificing her happiness,
her future,

15:18.051 --> 15:19.119
just because she knows --

15:19.152 --> 15:20.453
She's lying.

15:20.487 --> 15:21.989
She's lying.

15:22.022 --> 15:25.325
It could be either
reason number four or --

15:25.358 --> 15:26.994
No, she's not lying, Shaun.
She loves him.

15:27.027 --> 15:28.095
She doesn't love him.

15:28.128 --> 15:29.529
You haven't even met her!

15:29.562 --> 15:31.598
You haven't seen what she's like
with him, with their son.

15:31.631 --> 15:33.300
I'm not good
at reading people.

15:33.333 --> 15:35.735
Well, I am, and --
I think people-reading

15:35.768 --> 15:38.571
embraces personal biases.

15:38.605 --> 15:42.375
I think we should try
to avoid biases.

15:42.409 --> 15:45.145
Knowledge of human behavior

15:45.178 --> 15:48.281
can help us make
informed, intuitive decisions.

15:48.315 --> 15:50.283
Mm, my way is better.

15:50.317 --> 15:53.486
It's based on actions.
She's lying.

15:53.520 --> 15:54.687
All right.

15:54.721 --> 15:57.024
If you love someone,

15:57.057 --> 16:01.061
you'll do anything
to prevent their death.

16:01.094 --> 16:07.200
**

16:07.234 --> 16:09.202
This...situation --

16:09.236 --> 16:12.539
There seems to be
a conflict of interest.

16:12.572 --> 16:15.108
So I would like to bring in
someone else from legal

16:15.142 --> 16:17.044
to handle it.

16:17.077 --> 16:19.112
Yeah, I agree.

16:19.146 --> 16:21.548
You're an excellent lawyer,
but --

16:21.581 --> 16:24.084
But what?

16:24.117 --> 16:25.418
Do you think this
is my problem?

16:25.452 --> 16:27.120
It's understandable.

16:27.154 --> 16:28.421
48 hours ago,
we were engaged.

16:28.455 --> 16:30.057
And now, suddenly,

16:30.090 --> 16:31.224
you're supposed to be
investigating me?

16:31.258 --> 16:33.093
Yes.

16:33.126 --> 16:34.127
And doing crazy things,

16:34.161 --> 16:36.329
like expecting you
to give me complete answers

16:36.363 --> 16:37.764
to appropriate questions.

16:37.797 --> 16:40.300
You were trusting
Murphy's judgment over mine.

16:40.333 --> 16:42.469
His judgment about
my demeanor.

16:42.502 --> 16:44.404
Seriously?

16:44.437 --> 16:46.439
I asked you a question.

16:46.473 --> 16:47.507
You wanted me
to screw up.

16:47.540 --> 16:49.109
You did screw up.

16:49.142 --> 16:50.077
So what?

16:50.110 --> 16:53.680
So we just deal with it.

16:53.713 --> 16:56.216
But if you can't even admit that
you're not always perfect,

16:56.249 --> 16:58.151
then I --
I am not perfect!

16:58.185 --> 17:01.054
**

17:01.088 --> 17:03.323
Clearly, I have made mistakes
in my life.

17:03.356 --> 17:05.158
**

17:05.192 --> 17:06.726
But not this time.

17:06.759 --> 17:10.130
That punctured bronchus
was not my fault.

17:10.163 --> 17:16.236
**

17:16.269 --> 17:22.542
**

17:22.575 --> 17:27.814
[ Monitor beeping rhythmically ]

17:27.847 --> 17:31.218
The nurse says his vital signs
are stable.

17:31.251 --> 17:32.385
No change.

17:32.419 --> 17:33.720
Claire:
That's good.

17:37.457 --> 17:39.259
It's...

17:39.292 --> 17:42.695
such a great sacrifice

17:42.729 --> 17:46.699
to respect his wishes enough
to let him go.

17:46.733 --> 17:49.202
You must love your husband
very much.

18:00.713 --> 18:03.883
But...

18:03.916 --> 18:07.154
there could be
another explanation.

18:07.187 --> 18:11.691
Either you love him enough
to let him die...

18:11.724 --> 18:16.129
or you hate him enough
to let him die.

18:16.163 --> 18:19.832
You don't know
what you're talking about.

18:19.866 --> 18:24.637
There's a doctor here
who harassed me.

18:24.671 --> 18:27.374
He made me feel vulnerable,
worthless --

18:27.407 --> 18:31.778
neither of which I am.

18:31.811 --> 18:35.882
But he never hurt me.

18:35.915 --> 18:40.620
I can't imagine how I would feel
if he did,

18:40.653 --> 18:43.590
what I would do,

18:43.623 --> 18:46.259
what I would want
to do to him.

18:46.293 --> 18:49.629
**

18:49.662 --> 18:51.264
What did your husband
do to you?

18:51.298 --> 18:54.434
**

18:54.467 --> 18:57.270
He's a good father.

18:57.304 --> 18:59.439
No, he's not.

18:59.472 --> 19:01.774
A good father doesn't
hurt a mother.

19:01.808 --> 19:03.443
Payton loves him.

19:03.476 --> 19:04.344
All the more reason --

19:04.377 --> 19:05.845
No.

19:05.878 --> 19:08.915
Payton doesn't know anything.
He never can.

19:08.948 --> 19:11.751
I know you're afraid
he'll come after you,

19:11.784 --> 19:14.854
but there are people
who can help.

19:14.887 --> 19:20.893
**

19:20.927 --> 19:27.300
**

19:27.334 --> 19:29.436
Payton is better off with
the memory of a loving father

19:29.469 --> 19:30.803
than the truth.

19:37.244 --> 19:40.380
Let him die.

19:40.413 --> 19:47.920
**

19:47.954 --> 19:52.325
Methanol is causing
her abdominal pain.

19:52.359 --> 19:53.960
She drank wood alcohol?

19:53.993 --> 19:55.027
People drink whatever
they can drink.

19:55.061 --> 19:57.364
Well, she's Muslim --
Wouldn't let me touch her.

19:57.397 --> 19:59.466
Religious people aren't
immune to hypocrisy.

19:59.499 --> 20:03.603
There are other ways to explain
the presence of methanol.

20:03.636 --> 20:05.505
It's also produced
by the liver

20:05.538 --> 20:08.275
when the body is exposed
to certain caustic chemicals.

20:08.308 --> 20:11.311
If inhaled, caustic chemicals
could also inflame the lungs.

20:11.344 --> 20:13.246
And caustic chemicals
also burn,

20:13.280 --> 20:14.781
so it would explain
all her symptoms.

20:14.814 --> 20:16.283
Do you happen
to have a list

20:16.316 --> 20:17.517
of which caustic chemicals
do all that?

20:17.550 --> 20:19.986
Dimethyl sulfate --

20:20.019 --> 20:22.589
It's used in
the pharmaceutical industry.

20:22.622 --> 20:24.357
She's a school teacher.
It's also used

20:24.391 --> 20:26.526
in water treatment,
industrial pesticides,

20:26.559 --> 20:27.927
and chemical weapons.

20:27.960 --> 20:29.562
She has no reason
to be involved

20:29.596 --> 20:31.598
with water treatment
or industrial pesticides.

20:31.631 --> 20:33.733
But she could
be a school teacher

20:33.766 --> 20:34.834
and a terrorist.

20:34.867 --> 20:38.538
**

20:44.311 --> 20:44.944
So, what do we do?
The surgery.

20:44.977 --> 20:46.779
We don't have
her consent.

20:46.813 --> 20:49.048
Technically, the issue is
we don't have his consent.

20:49.081 --> 20:51.484
We go to his wife
because we can't get his,

20:51.518 --> 20:52.852
the assumption being that
she's operating

20:52.885 --> 20:54.321
in his best interests.

20:54.354 --> 20:57.557
Pretty sure that's not
happening here.

20:57.590 --> 20:58.925
Go back to the wife,
get her to change her mind,

20:58.958 --> 21:00.960
or we'll take it to court.

21:00.993 --> 21:02.962
Okay.

21:02.995 --> 21:04.464
Hey, you look annoyed.

21:04.497 --> 21:05.898
I'm annoyed
we're sending him home

21:05.932 --> 21:07.534
to keep abusing his wife.

21:07.567 --> 21:09.769
She's a world-class liar.

21:09.802 --> 21:11.771
I mean, for all we know,
she wants her husband dead

21:11.804 --> 21:13.973
so that she can run off
with her Pilates instructor.

21:14.006 --> 21:15.908
I'll get the consent.

21:15.942 --> 21:17.310
Thank you.

21:19.446 --> 21:22.515
[ Indistinct speaking over PA ]

21:22.549 --> 21:24.817
She refused initial treatment
for methanol toxicity.

21:24.851 --> 21:25.818
It's ethanol --

21:25.852 --> 21:27.454
Because she's Muslim,
she can't consume it.

21:27.487 --> 21:29.589
Shaun: She has alcohol
in her system

21:29.622 --> 21:31.624
but won't let us put alcohol
in her system to treat it,

21:31.658 --> 21:33.560
because she doesn't want alcohol
in her system.

21:33.593 --> 21:35.895
We put her on fomepi--
Dr. Murphy...

21:35.928 --> 21:37.797
Is this part of your evidence
that she's a terrorist?

21:37.830 --> 21:39.699
Because she's Muslim?

21:39.732 --> 21:41.634
There are billions of Muslims
that aren't terrorists.

21:41.668 --> 21:44.704
Is that part of your evidence
that she's not?

21:44.737 --> 21:47.073
I think she's a terrorist
because it's the easiest way

21:47.106 --> 21:48.875
to explain her symptoms
and her lie.

21:48.908 --> 21:51.043
Do you have a way?

21:51.077 --> 21:53.613
She had an accident.
It scared her.

21:53.646 --> 21:54.514
Maybe we scare her.

21:54.547 --> 21:56.783
Hell, maybe this whole place
scares her.

21:56.816 --> 21:58.685
There are a lot of reasons
people don't tell the truth

21:58.718 --> 21:59.852
other than
criminal activity.

21:59.886 --> 22:01.654
Six other reasons.

22:01.688 --> 22:04.090
If a person comes in
with a gunshot wound,

22:04.123 --> 22:05.825
we have to report it.

22:05.858 --> 22:07.360
Why don't we have
to report

22:07.394 --> 22:08.995
someone who might be making
chemical weapons?

22:09.028 --> 22:12.665
Because unfounded accusations
can destroy people's lives.

22:12.699 --> 22:15.368
What does it matter
what people speculate

22:15.402 --> 22:16.803
as long as the truth
comes out?

22:16.836 --> 22:18.405
Because people
make up their minds

22:18.438 --> 22:19.539
before the truth
comes out.

22:19.572 --> 22:21.541
Says the guy who played
the race card

22:21.574 --> 22:22.742
when he needed
an advantage.

22:22.775 --> 22:24.644
Even if you're right,

22:24.677 --> 22:27.514
she's not making bombs
while she's in our ICU.

22:27.547 --> 22:29.782
Also, you're wrong.
Now, keep me posted.

22:29.816 --> 22:31.851
If she's not better
in the next two hours,

22:31.884 --> 22:33.853
I want to know.

22:33.886 --> 22:40.427
**

22:45.097 --> 22:47.900
We need you to consent
to your husband's surgery.

22:50.537 --> 22:52.371
I said "no."

22:54.541 --> 22:58.445
There's a better way,
Tessa.

22:58.478 --> 23:00.112
Leave him.

23:00.146 --> 23:02.682
Start a new life.

23:08.755 --> 23:09.956
[ Voice breaking ]
I'm afraid.

23:09.989 --> 23:11.491
I know.

23:11.524 --> 23:14.193
But...this --

23:14.226 --> 23:17.630
This isn't the answer.

23:17.664 --> 23:19.666
[ Sighs ]
If you don't consent,

23:19.699 --> 23:20.733
we'll take this
to the court,

23:20.767 --> 23:23.803
and we'll tell a judge
what we know.

23:23.836 --> 23:26.172
I told you those things
in confidence.

23:26.205 --> 23:28.207
You are not my patient.
Your husband is.

23:28.240 --> 23:30.810
[ Scoffs ]

23:30.843 --> 23:33.513
Two things will happen.

23:33.546 --> 23:35.181
We wil get the consent,

23:35.214 --> 23:37.517
and Payton will find out
the truth.

23:37.550 --> 23:45.892
**

23:45.925 --> 23:54.066
**

23:54.100 --> 24:02.709
**

24:02.742 --> 24:10.950
**

24:10.983 --> 24:14.220
Tessa?

24:14.253 --> 24:18.558
You are stronger than
you think you are.

24:18.591 --> 24:23.663
**

24:23.696 --> 24:28.735
**

24:28.768 --> 24:31.638
[ Monitor beeping rhythmically ]

24:38.778 --> 24:41.914
Your methanol toxicity
is abating --

24:41.948 --> 24:43.850
The treatment's working.

24:43.883 --> 24:46.085
Great.

24:46.118 --> 24:49.689
Um...do you think that
I'll be able to leave soon?

24:49.722 --> 24:51.858
All of your symptoms
are consistent

24:51.891 --> 24:54.126
with exposure
to dimethyl sulfate.

24:54.160 --> 24:57.129
I -- I've never heard
of dimethyl --

24:57.163 --> 25:01.000
Dimethyl sulfate is used
to make chemical weapons.

25:02.935 --> 25:04.070
[ Scoffs ]

25:07.774 --> 25:11.611
I didn't expect this
from you.

25:11.644 --> 25:14.681
I made a statement.

25:14.714 --> 25:17.049
You're different.

25:17.083 --> 25:19.151
I have autism.

25:19.185 --> 25:21.253
You've experienced
bigotry.

25:21.287 --> 25:24.857
Yes.

25:24.891 --> 25:29.829
Have...people refused
to serve you?

25:29.862 --> 25:32.899
Have you seen people

25:32.932 --> 25:35.001
change their flight

25:35.034 --> 25:37.970
because of you?

25:38.004 --> 25:39.238
[ Voice breaking ]
Have people cursed you out

25:39.271 --> 25:41.774
before you've opened
your mouth?

25:41.808 --> 25:44.310
**

25:44.343 --> 25:46.613
I'm not prejudiced.

25:46.646 --> 25:48.615
I have evidence.

25:48.648 --> 25:51.350
Nobody's prejudiced.

25:51.383 --> 25:54.587
Everybody has evidence.

25:54.621 --> 25:57.223
And I'm always brown.

25:57.256 --> 25:59.358
[ Scoffs ]

25:59.391 --> 26:01.160
Maybe you're not
so different.

26:01.193 --> 26:03.696
**

26:03.730 --> 26:05.131
[ Inhales sharply ]

26:05.164 --> 26:08.768
You're sweating.

26:08.801 --> 26:11.137
Perspiration is a sign
of dishonesty.

26:11.170 --> 26:13.606
[ Breathing shakily ]

26:13.640 --> 26:14.306
[ Gasps ]

26:14.340 --> 26:15.908
My chest.

26:15.942 --> 26:18.210
Chest pain can be brought on
by anxiety.

26:18.244 --> 26:19.946
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]

26:19.979 --> 26:22.649
Oh, but this time,
you are having a heart attack.

26:22.682 --> 26:24.316
EKG, stat!

26:24.350 --> 26:27.253
**

26:27.286 --> 26:29.956
The endothelial lining
had moderate inflammation

26:29.989 --> 26:31.323
that appeared acute,

26:31.357 --> 26:34.060
and there was evidence
of mucosal edema.

26:34.093 --> 26:35.828
I made no extraordinary
motions,

26:35.862 --> 26:38.164
nor did I apply
any unnecessary force.

26:38.197 --> 26:40.199
And yet, the bronchus
was punctured.

26:40.232 --> 26:41.934
Which is a risk,
albeit a small one,

26:41.968 --> 26:43.269
with this kind
of procedure.

26:45.772 --> 26:46.806
Well...
[ Pen clicks ]

26:46.839 --> 26:48.641
thank you.

26:48.675 --> 26:50.877
I appreciate the thoroughness
of your answers.

26:50.910 --> 26:53.179
Not sure I understood
it all...
[ Chuckles ]

26:53.212 --> 26:57.016
...but I think
I've got what I need.

26:57.049 --> 27:00.352
I probably shouldn't
say anything,

27:00.386 --> 27:01.788
but I know
you and Ms. Preston

27:01.821 --> 27:03.122
are going through something
right now.

27:03.155 --> 27:04.423
That really
wasn't relevant.

27:04.456 --> 27:06.893
Oh, I-I know. I know.
It's just...

27:08.394 --> 27:11.731
I know she'll get through it,
but...

27:11.764 --> 27:14.667
it's good you're
handling it better.

27:14.701 --> 27:17.804
It's one thing to be distracted
while drafting a contract

27:17.837 --> 27:20.840
and a whole other thing entirely
doing what you do.

27:20.873 --> 27:24.977
**

27:25.011 --> 27:26.913
[ Footsteps depart ]

27:26.946 --> 27:29.782
**

27:29.816 --> 27:31.818
[ Door closes ]

27:31.851 --> 27:33.953
Inject dye.

27:33.986 --> 27:36.989
Injecting dye.

27:37.023 --> 27:40.292
[ Monitor beeping rhythmically ]

27:40.326 --> 27:42.661
Hanging a left
at the vertebral artery.

27:45.965 --> 27:49.301
Okay, withdrawing
the guide wire.

27:49.335 --> 27:50.970
Inserting
the platinum matrix.

27:51.003 --> 27:52.271
[ Monitor continues ]

27:55.742 --> 27:58.210
You know, sometimes,
you do the right thing

27:58.244 --> 28:00.379
and things get
a little better.

28:00.412 --> 28:02.715
And sometimes,
things still suck.

28:06.052 --> 28:10.790
Entering the aneurysm.

28:10.823 --> 28:12.224
Okay.

28:12.258 --> 28:13.325
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]

28:13.359 --> 28:14.260
Blood pressure's
spiking.

28:14.293 --> 28:15.261
Wait, why?

28:15.294 --> 28:17.129
There's no rupture,
no bleeding,

28:17.163 --> 28:18.397
no stroke.
[ Sighs ]

28:18.430 --> 28:21.400
If his BP goes up any higher,
he will have a stroke.

28:21.433 --> 28:23.135
[ Sighs ] I'm terminating
the procedure.

28:23.169 --> 28:26.138
Push 20 milligrams
of labetalol, stat.

28:26.172 --> 28:29.308
**

28:33.512 --> 28:35.047
We need to stabilize him before
we can retry the procedure,

28:35.081 --> 28:37.216
which means we need
to figure out what we missed.

28:37.249 --> 28:39.051
This wasn't our fault.

28:39.085 --> 28:41.287
His BP was stable
going in.

28:41.320 --> 28:42.889
He's been on
calcium-channel blockers

28:42.922 --> 28:44.423
for the last six years.
Well, we missed something.

28:44.456 --> 28:48.194
BP doesn't skyrocket
for no reason.

28:48.227 --> 28:49.361
Run a full work-up.

28:52.364 --> 28:54.500
Why would a 28-year-old
with no risk factors

28:54.533 --> 28:56.135
have a heart attack?

28:56.168 --> 28:57.269
Hmm.

28:57.303 --> 29:00.072
Her heart is burning.

29:00.106 --> 29:01.240
Burning?

29:01.273 --> 29:03.375
From the caustic
chemical!

29:03.409 --> 29:06.412
Murphy.
It's going
through her system.

29:06.445 --> 29:08.881
Unlike thermal burns,

29:08.915 --> 29:11.050
chemical burns
get worse over time.

29:11.083 --> 29:14.220
And it also explains
the punctured bronchus.

29:14.253 --> 29:16.522
The caustic chemical
thinned the bronchial walls.

29:16.555 --> 29:18.390
You did not make
a mistake.

29:18.424 --> 29:20.026
That's not the only
explanation.

29:21.327 --> 29:22.995
But I'll shut up now.

29:23.029 --> 29:24.230
You think you have
a good idea,

29:24.263 --> 29:26.933
but you're going
to shut yourself up?

29:26.966 --> 29:29.235
It could be caused
by an infection

29:29.268 --> 29:32.839
from bacteria that leaked
as a result of the puncture.

29:32.872 --> 29:36.408
The treatments are
diametrically opposed --

29:36.442 --> 29:39.011
antibiotics
if it's infection,

29:39.045 --> 29:41.147
steroids
if it's inflammation.

29:41.180 --> 29:44.150
If she needs antibiotics
and she needs steroids instead,

29:44.183 --> 29:45.417
it will suppress
her immune system,

29:45.451 --> 29:47.820
causing the infection
to flourish and kill her.

29:47.854 --> 29:49.421
If she needs steroids

29:49.455 --> 29:51.257
and we give her antibiotics,
then --

29:51.290 --> 29:52.458
I get it.

29:52.491 --> 29:53.425
We'd better be right.

29:53.459 --> 29:55.227
Yes.

29:55.261 --> 29:57.930
Sir, I think we should bring
another senior attending in

29:57.964 --> 30:00.099
to consult on this decision.
Why?

30:00.132 --> 30:02.168
Because if Shaun's right,
you're exonerated.

30:02.201 --> 30:03.502
And if I'm right,
you may have made the mistake

30:03.535 --> 30:06.005
that could kill
this woman.

30:06.038 --> 30:08.007
You don't think
I can be objective?

30:08.040 --> 30:10.042
I think you're incredibly
professional --

30:10.076 --> 30:10.809
Shut up, Jared.

30:14.947 --> 30:21.320
It is possible that
I screwed up.

30:21.353 --> 30:23.289
Let's put her on
broad-spectrum antibiotics.

30:23.322 --> 30:25.424
You're wrong.

30:25.457 --> 30:27.026
Making a decision

30:27.059 --> 30:29.095
on the assumption
you made a mistake

30:29.128 --> 30:29.996
is a mistake.

30:30.029 --> 30:33.599
You're very arrogant.

30:33.632 --> 30:35.968
It helps you
be a great surgeon.

30:38.204 --> 30:40.306
Fortunately, I don't need
your approval.

30:40.339 --> 30:45.577
**

30:48.915 --> 30:51.017
[ Door closes ]

30:51.050 --> 30:54.220
We've determined what
the underlying problem was.

30:54.253 --> 30:56.022
What caused your husband's
aneurysm to rupture

30:56.055 --> 30:58.424
and why his blood pressure
spiked in the O.R.

30:58.457 --> 31:01.193
According to his labs,
he hasn't been taking his meds.

31:01.227 --> 31:03.029
As far as I know,
he has.

31:03.062 --> 31:05.297
I mean, that's just
not like him.

31:05.331 --> 31:07.934
We don't think it's like him,
either.

31:10.602 --> 31:13.906
You think I had something
to do with this?

31:13.940 --> 31:16.375
That I, what,
threw his meds away?

31:16.408 --> 31:20.146
He'd just order more.

31:20.179 --> 31:23.482
But if you emptied his capsules
and filled them with sugar --

31:23.515 --> 31:26.185
or, even better, salt --

31:26.218 --> 31:28.220
It would end
your nightmare.

31:28.254 --> 31:31.123
**

31:31.157 --> 31:33.525
I was willing
to let him die,

31:33.559 --> 31:39.465
but I could never --

31:39.498 --> 31:43.335
If I were strong enough
to kill him...

31:43.369 --> 31:48.440
**

31:48.474 --> 31:54.180
**

31:54.213 --> 31:56.382
Is there a chance
your son knows more

31:56.415 --> 31:58.384
than you think he does?

31:58.417 --> 32:06.625
**

32:06.658 --> 32:15.234
**

32:15.267 --> 32:19.405
[ Monitor beeping ]

32:19.438 --> 32:21.040
Her heart rate's 90.

32:21.073 --> 32:22.975
That's in
the normal range.

32:23.009 --> 32:25.477
But it was 83.
It should be going down.

32:25.511 --> 32:28.180
All her other signs
are normal.

32:28.214 --> 32:31.150
You were right.
This is the proper treatment.

32:31.183 --> 32:32.318
95.

32:32.351 --> 32:36.022
[ Monitor quickens ]

32:36.055 --> 32:38.124
I'm switching her
to steroids.

32:38.157 --> 32:39.992
If we give her
steroids,

32:40.026 --> 32:42.194
it will suppress
her immune system,

32:42.228 --> 32:43.295
causing the infection
to flourish...

32:43.329 --> 32:45.197
I'm going to push 40 milligrams
of methylprednisolone.

32:45.231 --> 32:46.365
...and she'll die.

32:46.398 --> 32:48.167
**

32:48.200 --> 32:49.635
This is on me.

32:49.668 --> 32:51.437
I know.

32:51.470 --> 32:53.405
**

32:58.077 --> 33:00.246
**

33:00.279 --> 33:03.115
We switched her
to methylprednisolone.

33:03.149 --> 33:04.250
It's working.

33:04.283 --> 33:05.717
You were wrong.

33:05.751 --> 33:07.386
Yeah, I got that.

33:07.419 --> 33:09.788
Just about
the treatment choice.

33:09.821 --> 33:10.622
You didn't do anything wrong
in the O.R.

33:10.656 --> 33:12.324
Don't kiss my ass.

33:12.358 --> 33:17.296
Jared saved her life.

33:17.329 --> 33:19.531
If he hadn't acted so quickly,
she would've died,

33:19.565 --> 33:22.268
and that would've been
your fault.

33:22.301 --> 33:23.335
Yes, it would've.

33:23.369 --> 33:24.470
You should thank him.

33:32.211 --> 33:34.080
Thank you, Dr. Kalu.

33:40.286 --> 33:49.361
**

33:49.395 --> 33:58.704
**

33:58.737 --> 34:08.280
**

34:08.314 --> 34:17.489
**

34:29.168 --> 34:29.768
Hey.

34:29.801 --> 34:31.203
Can I help you?

34:31.237 --> 34:34.106
I'm Dr. Shaun Murphy.

34:34.140 --> 34:37.809
You're my new neighbor,
number 34.

34:37.843 --> 34:40.279
Yeah, cool.

34:40.312 --> 34:42.248
Uh, you wanna come in
for a beer?

34:42.281 --> 34:43.415
No.

34:43.449 --> 34:51.423
**

34:51.457 --> 34:53.392
Nice work.

34:53.425 --> 34:54.660
You, too.

34:54.693 --> 34:57.496
You can have
the honors.

34:57.529 --> 34:59.165
[ Sighs ]

34:59.198 --> 35:00.766
This is the first time
I'm not looking forward

35:00.799 --> 35:03.269
to telling the family
it went well.

35:03.302 --> 35:12.411
**

35:12.444 --> 35:21.320
**

35:21.353 --> 35:30.196
**

35:30.229 --> 35:32.198
You're going
to be fine.

35:32.231 --> 35:34.533
The treatment worked?

35:34.566 --> 35:37.436
The second one did.
The first one almost killed you.

35:37.469 --> 35:39.605
The fact that you're alive
right now is evidence

35:39.638 --> 35:41.340
that you were working
with dimethyl sulfate.

35:41.373 --> 35:45.944
You're a terrorist,
aren't you?

35:45.977 --> 35:49.515
My brother works
for a drug company.

35:49.548 --> 35:52.518
They use dimethyl sulfate to
make one of their medications.

35:52.551 --> 35:53.952
He stole some for me.

35:53.985 --> 35:56.522
So you could make
a chemical weapon.

35:56.555 --> 36:02.961
So I could make
perfume.

36:02.994 --> 36:04.196
Smell that.

36:17.309 --> 36:20.512
It's...beautiful.

36:20.546 --> 36:21.880
But very stupid.

36:21.913 --> 36:23.915
Yeah.

36:23.949 --> 36:26.552
Especially since my brother
would get fired

36:26.585 --> 36:27.753
if anyone ever found out.

36:29.888 --> 36:30.822
You believe her?

36:30.856 --> 36:32.958
Protecting someone --

36:32.991 --> 36:34.993
reason number three.

36:35.026 --> 36:37.529
**

36:37.563 --> 36:40.366
So...we good?

36:40.399 --> 36:42.534
Thing is, I'm not sure
it really matters.

36:42.568 --> 36:44.403
I've been told I can only have
three residents next year.

36:44.436 --> 36:45.404
That's great.

36:45.437 --> 36:46.838
Not really.

36:46.872 --> 36:49.575
Because of Coyle's transfer,
I have to take on his.

36:49.608 --> 36:51.910
Reznick?

36:51.943 --> 36:54.513
[ Laughs ]
She's a pain.

36:54.546 --> 36:56.848
Pain can be
a hell of motivator.

36:56.882 --> 36:57.749
Good luck.

37:04.490 --> 37:05.757
You were right.

37:08.460 --> 37:12.631
And I think you were right that
I wanted you to be wrong.

37:12.664 --> 37:15.401
And I'm sorry.

37:15.434 --> 37:18.604
You were right, too.

37:18.637 --> 37:22.441
I kept telling myself that
I'm fine, but...

37:22.474 --> 37:24.009
it's been hard.

37:24.042 --> 37:25.877
Got me second-guessing
myself,

37:25.911 --> 37:28.514
maybe affecting my judgment.

37:28.547 --> 37:31.317
I don't know.

37:31.350 --> 37:33.952
If we're hurting so bad,
maybe we made a mistake.

37:33.985 --> 37:36.622
**

37:36.655 --> 37:38.056
No.

37:38.089 --> 37:40.459
It just means that
what we had mattered.

37:40.492 --> 37:43.695
Doesn't mean
that it was right.

37:43.729 --> 37:46.398
I've also been
thinking that...

37:46.432 --> 37:48.700
arrogance does make me
a better surgeon.

37:51.036 --> 37:52.538
But it's not gonna make me
a better husband.

37:52.571 --> 37:55.674
**

37:55.707 --> 37:57.943
I'm sorry.

37:57.976 --> 38:03.982
**

38:04.015 --> 38:10.055
**

38:10.088 --> 38:12.491
Kristin?

38:12.524 --> 38:13.925
Hey, I'm Claire.

38:13.959 --> 38:15.361
Hi.

38:15.394 --> 38:18.964
Thanks.

38:18.997 --> 38:20.599
Um,

38:20.632 --> 38:26.037
I am doing some research
on Dr. Coyle --

38:26.071 --> 38:30.709
on the women who worked with him
and then quit.

38:30.742 --> 38:36.415
I got another offer
at SF Muni.

38:36.448 --> 38:40.786
I was harassed
by Dr. Coyle.

38:40.819 --> 38:42.754
And I think you were,
too.

38:42.788 --> 38:47.926
**

38:47.959 --> 38:53.098
**

38:53.131 --> 38:55.634
[ Sighs ]

38:55.667 --> 39:01.072
Doing the right thing can make
things a little better...

39:01.106 --> 39:03.609
especially if
we do it together.

39:03.642 --> 39:10.682
**

39:10.716 --> 39:12.984
[ Speaks indistinctly ]

39:13.018 --> 39:20.559
**

39:25.531 --> 39:27.966
I have a new neighbor.

39:27.999 --> 39:32.404
Hmm. So, Lea's
really gone, huh?

39:32.438 --> 39:35.474
So, can we have breakfast
tomorrow?

39:37.042 --> 39:39.678
I'd love to, Shaun,
but...

39:39.711 --> 39:42.781
[ Clears throat ]

39:42.814 --> 39:44.716
we, um...

39:44.750 --> 39:46.151
We talked about this,
right?

39:46.184 --> 39:49.120
I-I said that I would

39:49.154 --> 39:51.690
back off if you stayed,
right?

39:51.723 --> 39:52.691
More space,
less "fathering."

39:52.724 --> 39:53.992
I don't need a father.

39:54.025 --> 39:55.694
I hate fathers.

39:55.727 --> 39:56.662
Right, so --

39:56.695 --> 39:58.564
I need a friend.

40:03.502 --> 40:07.105
Shaun, I-I am someone
who can't help

40:07.138 --> 40:08.874
but give advice,
you know?

40:08.907 --> 40:12.410
I don't know
if I can not do that.

40:14.746 --> 40:18.684
So you think I can change
and you can't?

40:21.620 --> 40:24.155
I think that we have
a certain kind of relationship.

40:24.189 --> 40:26.858
And we can call it something
different if we want,

40:26.892 --> 40:29.595
but we can't magically
make it different.

40:29.628 --> 40:31.597
You said that
you wanted space.

40:31.630 --> 40:33.632
You said that
you needed space.

40:39.905 --> 40:45.243
I-I think you should
be my friend.

40:45.276 --> 40:50.649
[ Patrick Watson's
"Broken" plays ]

40:50.682 --> 40:52.150
Shaun...

40:52.183 --> 40:59.491
**

40:59.525 --> 41:06.598
**

41:06.632 --> 41:07.899
Okay.

41:07.933 --> 41:11.236
**

41:11.269 --> 41:13.171
Shaun?

41:13.204 --> 41:19.811
* Do you
feel a little broken? *

41:19.845 --> 41:26.552
* Do you
feel a little broken? *

41:26.585 --> 41:33.191
* Do you
feel a little broken? *

41:33.224 --> 41:41.633
* Do you feel a little
bro-o-ken? *

41:41.667 --> 41:47.205
* Memories come and they go

41:47.238 --> 41:54.312
* You just learn to let go

41:54.345 --> 41:59.751
* Sometimes, sometimes,
you wanna, wanna go back *

41:59.785 --> 42:04.055
What are you smelling
right now?

42:04.089 --> 42:05.757
Pine trees.

42:05.791 --> 42:07.926
* Do you
feel a little broken? *

42:07.959 --> 42:09.127
Mmm.

42:09.160 --> 42:12.230
**

42:12.263 --> 42:17.202
* Do you
feel a little broken? *

42:22.908 --> 42:32.584
**

42:32.618 --> 42:41.860
**

42:41.893 --> 42:51.202
**
